Full Title: 5th Conference on Intercultural Rhetoric and Discourse 
Short Title: CIRD5 

Date: 11-Jun-2009 - 13-Jun-2009
Location: Ann Arbor, MI, USA 
Contact Person: Christine Feak
Meeting Email: CIRD5@umich.edu
Web Site: http://legacyweb.lsa.umich.edu/eli/eli1/CIRD5/index.html 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics; Discourse Analysis; Pragmatics;
Text/Corpus Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 02-Feb-2009 

Meeting Description:

5th Conference on Intercultural Rhetoric and Discourse
English Language Institute
University of Michigan 
Ann Arbor, Michigan
June 11 - 13, 2009 

Call for Papers

Focus
We hope that the conference papers will focus on the way contextual occasions
affect communicative and textual outcomes across a wide range of intercultural
settings, from "small cultures" such as those that emerge in classrooms or
working groups, to broad cross-cultural comparisons (i.e. business) and
cross-disciplinary differences.

Plenary Speakers
Ulla Connor
Director, Indiana Center for Intercultural Communication,Indiana
University-Purdue University Indianapolis (IUPUI)

Fethi Helal
University of Tunis, Tunis, Tunisia

Priscilla Rogers
Stephen M. Ross School of Business, University of Michigan. Ann Arbor, Michigan

Conference Organizer
Christine Feak (cfeak@umich.edu)
English Language Institute
Telephone: 734-647-o483
FAX: 734-763-0369

Conference Website: http://www.lsa.umich.edu/eli (Click on 5th Conference on
Intercultural Rhetoric and Discourse under News) 

Abstracts
Abstracts are welcome in any area of intercultural rhetoric and discourse,
ranging from "small cultures" such as a classroom to larger settings.  Abstracts
should be 250 words or less and include a title, author name, a separate 50-word
summary, and A-V equipment needs. Submit proposal materials by e-mail to
CIRD5@umich.edu. Presenters will have 30 minutes plus 15 minutes to respond to
questions and comments.

Abstract Submission Deadline: February 2, 2009
Acceptance Notification: March 2, 2009


 





